== Events == * {{ill|Kannin|ja|寛仁|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1017]] {{ill|April 15|ja|4月15日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The eldest son of {{ill|Fujiwara no Michinaga|ja|藤原道長|12=draft|12=draft}} (namely, {{ill|Yoritomo|ja|藤原頼通|12=draft|12=draft}}) was appointed regent. * [[Jōan (era)|承安]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1174]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Emperor {{ill|Go-Shirakawa|ja|後白河法皇|12=draft|12=draft}} visited the separate villa of {{ill|Taira no Kiyomori|ja|平家|12=draft|12=draft}}. * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1561]] _month_ day) – Nagao Kagetora received a mandate from Uesugi Norimasa, was appointed Kantō Kanrei, and changed his name to Uesugi Kenshin. * {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|12=draft|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1600]] {{ill|April 29|ja|4月29日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Dutch ship “Leifde” drifted ashore in Bungo Province during a period of military mobilization led by William Adams (Eiroku period).
