{{Lunisolar March|qq=}}
'''March 16''' is the 16th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=|12=draft}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Kannin|ja|寛仁|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1017]] {{ill|April 15|ja|4月15日|qq=|12=draft}}) – The eldest son of {{ill|Fujiwara no Michinaga|ja|藤原道長|qq=|12=draft}} (namely, {{ill|Yoritomo|ja|藤原頼通|qq=|12=draft}}) was appointed regent.
* [[Jōan (era)|承安]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1174]] {{ill|April 19|ja|4月19日|qq=|12=draft}}) – Emperor {{ill|Go-Shirakawa|ja|後白河法皇|qq=|12=draft}} visited the separate villa of {{ill|Taira no Kiyomori|ja|平家|qq=|12=draft}}.
* [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1561]] _month_ day) – Nagao Kagetora received a mandate from Uesugi Norimasa, was appointed Kantō Kanrei, and changed his name to Uesugi Kenshin.
* {{ill|Keichō|ja|慶長|qq=|12=draft}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1600]] {{ill|April 29|ja|4月29日|qq=|12=draft}}) – The Dutch ship “Leifde” drifted ashore in Bungo Province during a period of military mobilization led by William Adams (Eiroku period).
== Births ==
* {{ill|Bunka|ja|文政|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1806]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|qq=|12=draft}}) – Fujita Tōko, a Confucian scholar (died [[1855]]).
* {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1832]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|qq=|12=draft}}) – Furukawa Shihei, a businessperson who founded the Furukawa conglomerate (died [[1903]]).
== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文|qq=|12=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1662]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|qq=|12=draft}}) – Matsudaira Nobutsuna, a Rōjū of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[1596]]).
