ngo Province during a period of military mobilization led by William Adams (Eiroku period). == Births == * {{ill|Bunka|ja|文政|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1806]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – Fujita Tōko, a Confucian scholar (died [[1855]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1832]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – Furukawa Shihei, a businessperson who founded the Furukawa conglomerate (died [[1903]]). == Deaths == * {{ill|Kanbun|ja|寛文|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1662]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – Matsudaira Nobutsuna, a Rōjū of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[1596]]). == Commemorations == == See Also == {{Lunar Calendar See Also|3|15|3|17|2|16|4|3|0316|qq=}}
