{{Not to be confused with|March 16|qq=March 16}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月十六|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 16일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 16''' is the 16th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|qq=}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Kannin|Kannin]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1017|1017]] [[:en:April 15|April 15]]) – The eldest son of [[:en:Fujiwara no Michinaga|Fujiwara no Michinaga]] (namely, [[:en:Fujiwara no Yorimichi|Yoritomo]]) was appointed regent. * [[Jōan (era)|承安]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1174]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – Emperor {{ill|Go-Shirakawa|ja|後白河法皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Go-Shirakawa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 後白河天皇}} visited the separate villa of [[Taira no Kiyomori]]{{citation needed |平家|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Kiyomori|qq=}}. * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1561]] _month_ day) – Nagao Kagetora received a mandate from Uesugi Norimasa, was appointed Kantō Kanrei, and changed his name to Uesugi Kenshin. * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1600]] [[:en:April 29|April 29]]) – The Dutch ship “Leifde” drifted ashore in Bungo Province during a period of military mobilization led by William Adams (Eiroku period). == Births == * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunka]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1806]] [[:en:May 4|May 4]]) – Fujita Tōko, a Confucian scholar (died [[1855]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1832]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – Furukawa Shihei, a businessperson who founded the Furukawa conglomerate (died [[1903]]). == Deaths == * [[:en:Kanbun (era)|Kanbun]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1662]] [[:en:May 4|May 4]]) – Matsudaira Nobutsuna, a Rōjū of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[1596]]). == Commemorations == == See Also == {{Lunar Calendar See Also|3|15|3|17|2|16|4|3|0316|qq=}}
