== Events == * [[:en:Kannin|Kannin]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1017|1017]] [[:en:April 15|April 15]]) – The eldest son of [[:en:Fujiwara no Michinaga|Fujiwara no Michinaga]] (namely, [[:en:Fujiwara no Yorimichi|Yoritomo]]) was appointed regent. * [[Jōan (era)|承安]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1174|1174]] [[:en:April 19|April 19]]) – Emperor {{ill|Go-Shirakawa|ja|後白河法皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Go-Shirakawa|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 後白河天皇}} visited the separate villa of [[Taira no Kiyomori]]{{citation needed |平家|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Kiyomori|qq=}}. * [[:en:Eiroku|Eiroku]] 4th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1561|1561]] _month_ day) – Nagao Kagetora received a mandate from Uesugi Norimasa, was appointed Kantō Kanrei, and changed his name to Uesugi Kenshin. * [[:en:Keichō|Keichō]] 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1600|1600]] [[:en:April 29|April 29]]) – The Dutch ship “Leifde” drifted ashore in Bungo Province during a period of military mobilization led by William Adams (Eiroku period). == Births == * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunka]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1806]] [[:en:May 4|May 4]]) – Fujita Tōko, a Confucian scholar (died [[1855]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1832]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – Furukawa Shihei, a businessperson who founded the Furukawa conglomerate (died [[1903]]). == Deaths == * [[:en:Kanbun (era)|Kanbun]] 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1662]] [[:en:May 4|May 4]]) – Matsudaira Nobutsuna, a Rōjū of the Tokugawa shogunate (born [[:en:1596|1596]]). == Commemorations == == See Also == {{Lunar Calendar See Also|3|15|3|17|2|16|4|3|0316|qq=}}
