'''March 16''' is the 16th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Shakkō|ja|赤口|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shakkō|1=Shakkō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11635368}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Kannin|en|Kannin|qid=Q1193951|lt=Kannin|1=Kannin}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1017|en|1017|qid=Q19249|lt=1017|1=1017}} {{ill|April 15|en|April 15|qid=Q2497|lt=April 15|1=April 15}}) – The eldest son of {{ill|Fujiwara no Michinaga|en|Fujiwara no Michinaga|qid=Q433133|lt=Fujiwara no Michinaga|1=Fujiwara no Michinaga}} (namely, {{ill|Fujiwara no Yorimichi|en|Fujiwara no Yorimichi|qid=Q1370620|lt=Yoritomo|1=Fujiwara no Yorimichi}}) was appointed regent.
* {{ill|Jōan (era)|en|Jōan (era)|qid=Q1194188|lt=承安|1=Jōan (era)}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1174|en|1174|qid=Q19690|lt=1174|1=1174}} {{ill|April 19|en|April 19|qid=Q2523|lt=April 19|1=April 19}}) – Emperor {{ill|Go-Shirakawa|ja|後白河法皇|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Go-Shirakawa|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 後白河天皇|1=Emperor Go-Shirakawa|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q317984}} visited the separate villa of [[Taira no Kiyomori]]{{citation needed |平家|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taira no Kiyomori|qq=}}.
* {{ill|Eiroku|en|Eiroku|qid=Q1143341|lt=Eiroku|1=Eiroku}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1561|en|1561|qid=Q6618|lt=1561|1=1561}} _month_ day) – Nagao Kagetora received a mandate from Uesugi Norimasa, was appointed Kantō Kanrei, and changed his name to Uesugi Kenshin.
* {{ill|Keichō|en|Keichō|qid=Q1328185|lt=Keichō|1=Keichō}} 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1600|en|1600|qid=Q6720|lt=1600|1=1600}} {{ill|April 29|en|April 29|qid=Q2535|lt=April 29|1=April 29}}) – The Dutch ship “Leifde” drifted ashore in Bungo Province during a period of military mobilization led by William Adams (Eiroku period).
== Births ==
* {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|qid=Q1327119|lt=Bunka|1=Bunsei}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1806|en|1806|qid=Q6903|lt=1806|1=1806}} {{ill|May 4|en|May 4|qid=Q2549|lt=May 4|1=May 4}}) – Fujita Tōko, a Confucian scholar (died {{ill|1855|en|1855|qid=Q7673|lt=1855|1=1855}}).
* {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1832|en|1832|qid=Q7584|lt=1832|1=1832}} {{ill|April 16|en|April 16|qid=Q2519|lt=April 16|1=April 16}}) – Furukawa Shihei, a businessperson who founded the Furukawa conglomerate (died {{ill|1903|en|1903|qid=Q2045|lt=1903|1=1903}}).
== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Kanbun (era)|en|Kanbun (era)|qid=Q1146228|lt=Kanbun|1=Kanbun (era)}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1662|en|1662|qid=Q7574|lt=1662|1=1662}} {{ill|May 4|en|May 4|qid=Q2549|lt=May 4|1=May 4}}) – Matsudaira Nobutsuna, a Rōjū of the Tokugawa shogunate (born {{ill|1596|en|1596|qid=Q6785|lt=1596|1=1596}}).
